name: Dear Saint Gilda
description:
/Dear Saint Gilda:
I do not regret this love
Love is a miracle 
and I loved you./

Gilda was a sweet girl born under the name of Myriam in a quiet town called Villa Paranacito.
Gilda worked as a kindergarten teacher before her fame skyrocketed into the Tropical Scene.
Gilda was a singer, dancer, and performer. And the soul inside her soft Cumbia music spoke right to people's hearts. 
The day of her tragic death, crowds gathered spontaneously on Ruta de la Muerte and created an altar in her name. It keeps receiving offerings 25 years later.

Gilda is a Saint of the People: her printed presence brings miracles to life.
Holding Gilda close to your heart attracts prosperity and unconditional love.
